examples: We lead him to our chief
can you take me to the main entrance?
He conducted us to the palace

definitions.text: have as a result or residue
examples: The water left a mark on the silk dress
Her blood left a stain on the napkin
This remark lead to further arguments among the guests

definitions.text: travel in front of; go in advance of others
examples: The procession was headed by John

definitions.text: cause to undertake a certain action
examples: Her greed led her to forge the checks

definitions.text: stretch out over a distance, space, time, or scope; run or extend between two points or beyond a certain point
examples: Service runs all the way to Cranbury
His knowledge doesn't go very far
My memory extends back to my fourth year of life
The facts extend beyond a consideration of her personal assets
Who is heading this project?

definitions.text: be ahead of others; be the first
examples: she topped her class every year
The use of computers in the classroom lead to better writing

definitions.text: lead, as in the performance of a composition
examples: conduct an orchestra; Barenboim conducted the Chicago symphony for years
This door goes to the basement
The road runs South

definitions.text: move ahead (of others) in time or space
cause something to pass or lead somewhere
examples: Run the wire behind the cabinet
John moderated the discussion

definitions.text: (of panes of glass) fixed in place by means of thin strips of lead
examples: leaded windowpanes
leaded gasoline
leaded zinc

definitions.text: having thin strips of lead between the lines of type
